# Named Cursor Rules — Conventions

## Goals
- Make each rule discoverable, self-explanatory, and easy to discuss in PRs/issues.
- Use **numeric prefixes** for ordering and **short slugs** for purpose.

## File name pattern
`NN-category-purpose.mcp`
- `NN`: 2-digit sort order (00–99)
- `category`: foundation | architecture | style | ci | docs | security | storage | aiogram | collab
- `purpose`: 1–3 short words

### Examples (good)
- 00-foundation.mcp
- 01-architecture.mcp
- 02-style-python.mcp
- 03-style-aiogram.mcp
- 04-style-storage.mcp
- 05-style-docs.mcp
- 06-style-ci.mcp
- 07-style-security.mcp
- 08-collab-operational-protocol.mcp
- 09-collab-shared-context.mcp

### Anti-examples (avoid)
- rules.mcp
- misc.mcp
- temp-guidelines.mcp

## Rule anatomy
- Keep each rule **≤ 150 lines**; split if larger.
- Prefer **specific globs** over global `**/*` unless necessary.
- Use `alwaysApply: true` **only** for non-negotiable constraints (e.g., public API, security).
